Ramos Urges Congress to Pass Bills on Social Reform 
Philippine President Fidel Ramos today called on the congress to
expedite the passage of pending bills on the common legislative agenda
of the administration and congress to accelerate the social reform
program.
At today's meeting of the legislative-executive development advisory
council, the president specifically asked the Senate for the
expeditious passage of the irrigation crisis act which will authorize
major irrigation projects to be built through negotiated contract.
He stressed that the speedy passage of the bill will give a big boost
to the government's food security program.
